Positive review:
Breakfast was amazing. 11 euros was the best money I could've spent that day anywhere. There were few other options in the immediate area on a Saturday AM so the quality and selections  was greatly appreciated.  Exceeded expectations.

Also the coffee shop and lobby are nice to relax or get a refreshment even if you're not staying there.  The restaurant next door is a convenient option for a quick bite. They also have continuous room service in the hotel. We stayed on the 2nd floor and noise was reasonable other than a few doors or late talkers in the hall.  

Location was pretty enjoyable and relaxing
Negative review:
Got back to the hotel at 7pm on Friday and there was no parking available, but they had already charged me €10 for the night.  So the next day they were able to give me a partial refund during checkout.  I should've argued this when I got back there to be honest but was tired and didn't think straight, yet mentioned my concern in the morning.  The hotel garage is small, so be aware if you're bringing a car or rental, especially for multiple nights.

We asked for early check in since we had a morning flight to get to Ireland, they wouldn't give us a time or ETA when I asked the front desk around 11am, so a bit unhelpful until I'd asked a third time.  but in the end they did let us check in an hour early.

Bed was disappointing to say the least... also most hotel amenities were pretty sparse.  But other than that had a cozy stay.

Review title: Perfect location if visiting Bord Gáis Theatre/ Aviva Stadium. It is not walking distance from City Centre. Lovely r
Positive review: Property was in walking distance to the Bord Gáis Theatre and plenty of bars. The complementary rituals soaps and body lotions was a lovely touch. Fantastic size double bed. The Canal Express is also very handy for a quick take away coffee and snack, which is in the reception area. Exceptional breakfast - plenty for vegetarians!
Negative review: It was very costly. I think the parking should be included in the room rate - it’s €10 per day. Staff were quite slow at checking us in. Items in the vending machines were an extortionate price. The hotel bar was also disappointing as we paid €11.50 for a pornstar martini which was actually pre-made from a can and did not come with Prosecco. It did not taste great. Bartender said that it wouldn’t pay them to keep the ingredients for the drink in stock and that it was also an issue with training their staff. If you can’t give a customer a decent freshly made cocktail for the price they were charging - it shouldn’t be on the cocktail menu!
Property reply:
Dear Guest, 
Thank you for your feedback. I am delighted that you found the hotel to be in a good location for you and that you enjoyed Canal Express. Our vending machines are there for convenience so that guests have access to products on their floor without coming to Reception, we do not own the machines and so cannot dictate the prices, we also offer a full range of drinks and chocolate/ crisps at the Canal Express that you mentioned. Our carpark is charged at € 10.00 per night, this is quite reasonable in comparison to some of the hotel carparks in the city. Some of our rates do include the overnight parking, it depends on which one is chosen at the time of booking. I am sorry that you didn't enjoy the cocktail in the bar. We offer Craft Cocktails, 1661 which is a new and popular brand. We have had some great feedback on the taste and consistency of the cocktails since we started stocking them but I will ensure our Bar Manager is aware of your feedback. Thank you for letting us know your thoughts, it is always great to receive feedback like that so that we can improve our offering. 

Kind Regards

Donna Curry

Review title: From checking in at ease to the breakfast team & Chefs looking after us each morning, housekeeping team keeping our
Positive review: Everything
Negative review: Nothing

the property was nice in a good location but when I arrived it was quiet late as my flight got delayed but I had emailed to say I’d be late in and confirmed my stay twice, the boy at the desk told me that your systems crashed that day and he couldn’t explain what happened but told me I couldn’t stay and my room was given to someone else. as a young women travelling by myself obviously I was frightened as I don’t know my way around dublin and it was maybe 1 o clock in the morning. he said I could wait at a hotel in this chain but I’d have to get a taxi there and it was about 20 minutes away. he wasn’t very helpful and I was in a lot of distress as I was travelling all day and booked this hotel as I had an appointment the following day 3 minutes walk away. after a while when he seen how distressed and upset I was about the situation he some how got mixed up and there was actually a room for me. all the rest of the staff were lovely and the room was very nice.
Property reply:
Dear Guest, 
I am sorry that you had a bad experience when you arrived at the hotel. As you describe, when you arrived at the hotel our system had just crashed resulting in a glitch. At no stage was your room given to another guest, but unfortunately it was not showing as available. After offering to accommodate you, and organise a taxi, he was able to manually figure out which room was available and empty. I am sorry that this took some time. I am glad that you found all of the other team members to be nice and hope that you enjoyed the complimentary breakfast that our Night Manager arranged for you. If you are travelling to Dublin again in the near future, please do not hesitate to contact us directly on salesoffice@grandcanalhotel.com and we can arrange a complimentary upgrade if at all possible. 
Kind Regards
Donna Curry

Positive review: Comfortable beds and decent sized room. Walk-in shower (disabled with problems climbing into over-bath shower) eventually wrangled. Serving staff in restaurant were lovely.
Negative review: Building works being done and horrible noise in room. Attitude of duty manager being "You paid Booking not us" when pointed out how our weekend had been spoiled and how much we had paid for the room vs what we were getting. Swapping of rooms that left us without the needed walk-in shower. The free dinner and one one breakfast (out of two days) were not nearly enough for a ruined weekend. This hotel does NOT understand the meaning of the word DISABILITY.
Property reply:
Dear Guest, 
I am sorry that you did not enjoy your stay. Unfortunately, we received no advance notice that you required a room adapted for less abled guests. We did not have one prepared. The room that you were offered at 2.30pm was next to renovation works that were due to stop at 4pm. When this was not acceptable there were limited options left to the team. As a gesture for your dissatisfaction an evening meal and breakfast were provided, I am sorry that you did not feel this was adequate. Our team will always go above and beyond to ensure guests are looked after but if we do not know in advance of specific requirements, it can be difficult. 
Kind Regards
Donna Curry

Negative review: I like a cold room to sleep in but it was cold cold. Not a lick of heat on and it's February in Ireland. Shower was frustratingly tepid. Staff were questionable. Asked for a room anywhere but the third floor due to the construction on/below that floor. They said none was available. Asked if I checked in later would a room be available. They said yes, but either the room computer system is so poorly designed the staff can't tell what rooms will be available later (doubtful), or the staff lacked the training to read the system and what rooms would be available or they just lied. Came back after working a night shift and was stuck on the third floor. It was too late to cancel at that stage. And the construction drills started an hour earlier than we were told. Got a dishonest vibe off the staff since my travel partner who arrived the night before had a similar experience. All I was looking for was a clean, quiet bed and a hot shower in the morning. I won't be back again anytime soon.

Review title: Lage etwas außerhalb, aber noch zentral genug um die Innenstadt zu Fuß zu erreichen
Positive review: Optisch sehr ansprechend, sauber und die Lage gut. Die Betten waren bequem und schön waren auch die kleinen Körperpflegeprodukte von Rituals. Es war eine Kapselkaffeemaschine im Zimmer, Kaffeetassen, Milch, Zucker und eine Bügelsation. Die Fenster zu Straße sind doppelt verglast und dämmen sehr gut. WLAN war in unserem Zimmer etwas schwach, aber ausreichend. Gepäckraum ist vorhanden und mit Abholscheinen wird eine Verwechslung ausgeschlossen. Es kann vor Ort gefrühstückt werden und ein Restaurant ist auch direkt am Hotel (wir haben beides nicht genutzt). Zu Fuß benötigten wir ca. 30 min. bis zum Temple Bar Viertel. Die nächste Apotheke und ein Supermarkt ist in fünf Minuten zu Fuß erreichbar. Wir sind mit dem Dublin Express vom Flughafen bis Haltestelle Merrion Square Park gefahren (ca. 45 min.) und dann mit Gepäck bis zum Hotel nochmal ca. 10 min. zu Fuß. Es gibt in der Nähe eine Citybike-Verleihstation, so dass man mit dem Rad noch schneller in die Innenstadt gelangt (der Verkehr ist allerdings sehr rege, vor allem sehr viele Busse sind unterwegs).
Negative review: Wir hatten ein Familienzimmer (drei Betten in einem Zimmer). Keine Klimaanlage und die Luft war mit drei Personen im Zimmer etwas knapp. Unser Fenster war Richtung Straße und wir haben die erste Nacht bei geschlossenem Fenster, die zweite wegen Sauerstoffmangel bei offenem Fenster geschlafen. Der Verkehrslärm ist natürlich hörbar, doch wir waren so müde, dass uns das nichts ausgemacht hat.
Property reply:
Dear Guest, 
Thank you for your lovely comments about our hotel. I am sorry that you found the air to be an issue in the room and required the window to be open at night time. I appreciated your feedback.
Kind Regards

Donna Curry

I had to call booking . Com but they still didn't care. Won't be back in the hotel as the reception staff had no regard for me. So now I'm out €550 euro for one night. And haven't received a refund and they didn't try and resolve it they literally didn't care.
Property reply:

I have checked and the Receptionist was correct, the room was a 'NO PRE-PAYMENT REQUIRED' booking, this means that payment was due on arrival. Our Reservations Manager will contact Booking.com to investigate why you have been charged. If you have difficulty with contacting Booking.com, please do not hesitate to get in touch with us and we will see if we can assist. The hotel did not charge anything in advance of your stay and has only received the payment that you made on the front desk.

Review title: Замечательный отель с дружелюбным персоналом и невероятный завтрак
Positive review: Номер превзошел наши ожидания, очень просторно, все выглядит очень чисто и аккуратно, приятное постельное белье, и замечательная косметика Rituals для гостей. Было очень тихо, не мешал ни шум с улицы, ни другие гости. Заселение прошло очень быстро и дружелюбно, и когда мы останавливались в этом же отеле спустя две недели, мы попросили себе тот же номер, что и в первый раз - и отель удовлетворил нашу просьбу. Завтрак щаслуживает отдельных похвал - сервис официантов на высоте, отличный выбор еды, и все очень вкусно - из всех отелей, где мы оставнавливались в Ирландии, именно здесь завтрак понравился нам больше всего. Расположение такое, что придется чуток пройтись до центра (минут 15), но это того стоит, чтобы быть подальше от шума пабов. Очень рекомендую и с удовольствием остановлюсь там снова :)

Property reply:
Dear Guest, 
I am sorry that you had a negative experience at our hotel. From our records of your stay in November it is noted that two of our night staff went to the floor immediately-they found the gentleman in a different area on the corridor so may not have notified you of their arrival while they dealt with the person. The guest that was knocking on your room had made a mistake with the floor number which unfortunately is out of our control, instead of 513 he was knocking at your door on a lower floor. I am sorry that you felt that it took a long time for your call to be actioned.  We do have sufficient night staff on duty to action calls immediately, we also have double bolts on all doors as well as a key card operated system for the lifts which makes our hotel safer than most for guests. 

Kind Regards

Donna Curry

Dear Guest, 
I am delighted that you enjoyed your stay overall. Unfortunately, unless a credit card is registered at the front desk payment is requested at the restaurant. I was advised to park several blocks away without any offer of 'leave your luggage with us' etc. I asked if I could be contacted once people left the parking and was never called. I was also not offered any help getting a taxi that evening as most hotels in Dublin and other cities would do, but considering there were racially charged riots in Dublin the weekend before, I thought they might like to look after their guests better.
Property reply:
Dear Guest, 
I am very sorry to learn of your negative experience with our Reception Team. I have spoken to our team and can assure you that we will work to improve the experience for our guests at check in and  check out. We have an online taxi booking system so there is never an issue with reserving taxis,  usually there are several parked outside the door. I am sorry that not enough assistance with luggage or parking was forthcoming. Thank you for taking time to send us your review, which is very helpful as we continue to improve our service. 
Kind Regards

Donna Curry
